# Skills System

When performing tasks, check if any available skill can help. Invoke via shell:
`npx openskills read <skill-name>`

Available skills:

- brainstorming - Use before any creative work
- dispatching-parallel-agents - For 2+ independent parallel tasks
- executing-plans - Execute written implementation plans
- finishing-a-development-branch - Guide branch completion
- receiving-code-review - Process code review feedback
- requesting-code-review - Verify work meets requirements
- subagent-driven-development - Execute plans with independent tasks
- systematic-debugging - Debug before proposing fixes
- test-driven-development - Before writing implementation code
- using-git-worktrees - Isolate feature work
- verification-before-completion - Verify before claiming done
- writing-plans - Plan before touching code
- writing-skills - Create/edit skills
